Hungary Mulls Compensation for Wage Rise Above CPI, Varga Says

-- B y   Z o l t a n   S i m o n
-- 
2011-09-23T05:55:30Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-23/hungary-mulls-compensation-for-wage-rise-above-cpi-varga-says.html
Hungary’s government is considering
compensation for small and medium-sized companies for minimum
wage increases that exceed the inflation rate,  Mihaly Varga ,
Prime Minister Viktor Orban’s chief of staff, told M1 television
today.  The government has proposed an 18 percent increase in the
minimum wage for next year, more than four times the Cabinet’s
4.2 percent average inflation forecast for 2012.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Zoltan Simon at 
 zsimon@bloomberg.net  